      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-story&#34;&gt;The story&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cyanobacteria are a common marine bacteria that are often called blue-green algae, most of us are familiar with them for their tendency to cause toxic algal blooms. &lt;a href=&#34;sites.lsa.umich.edu/vecchiarelli-lab&#34;&gt;Dr. Anthony Vecchiarelli&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;twitter.com/CellfOrganized&#34;&gt;@CellfOrganized&lt;/a&gt;, studies them for their carboxysomes. Carboxysomes are icosahedron-shaped organelles packed with the carbon-fixing enzyme rubisco.&lt;/p&gt;














&lt;figure  id=&#34;figure-icosahedron-sourcehttpscommonswikimediaorgwikifilezeroth_stellation_of_icosahedronpng&#34;&gt;
  &lt;div class=&#34;d-flex justify-content-center&#34;&gt;
