  &lt;/div&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;
      Icosahedron &lt;a href=&#34;https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Zeroth_stellation_of_icosahedron.png&#34;&gt;Source&lt;/a&gt;.
    &lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Carboxysomes condense rubisco within a shell that allows carbon dixoide in, while blocking oxygen, which reduces rubisco&amp;rsquo;s rate of carbon fixation. Both actions increase the rate of carbon fixation to such an extent that only 2.5 mL of cyanobacteria can fix the same amount of carbon as a full-grown tree.&lt;/p&gt;














